verbose_text: miRNA-146a expression is induced in response to lipopolysaccharide (LPS) and pro inflammatory mediators in THP-1 cells and this induction is regulated by nuclear factor (NF)-kappaB, which in turn downregulates inflammatory cascades by decreasing the expression of IL-1 receptor associated kinase-1 (IRAK1) and tumor necrosis factor (TNF) receptor associated factor 6 (TRAF6).
